<br>
The father tested the mutation on himself before Bruce was born, but it didn't seem to work until he extracted some factor from Bruce's blood that had been activated by Bruce's exposure to the gamma rays.  Once he had injected this extra factor into himself and activated it through the gamma rays, he became some kind of elemental mutant and was able to take on the form of whatever substance he touched.<br>
<br>
When he visits Bruce at the end, he absorbs the electricity from the wire and gains strength; then he becomes an air elemental, then water.<br>
<br>
But I don't understand what happens to him when he tries to absorb all Bruce's energy.  He gets bigger and bigger and Bruce tells him to take it all ... and then what happens?  Seems like the father dies then but I got lost how it happened...  Did anybody get that? <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><br>
